The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 30 September is 388,342 (689.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 26 September, there were 33,212 new confirmed cases (59.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 19 September, there were 23,634 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 41% (9578 extra cases).
